the product came  sooner than was expected and it was packaged  the same way as I seen it in sears and home depot . the big difference  was the price 58 percent less than at both those stores .the skinny same great product  for more than half the price  what a bargain .

Stuck shop vac hose in dryer end and fed the brush from the outside using lowest drill speed.  it pulled itself through the the entire pipe. reviewText: Because our house builder was an idiot we have a very long dryer run. Even with cleaning the lint tray every load, the vent was filled with lint after 4 years. reviewText: Cleaned my dryer vent from the outside in, unfortunately the hose on my shopvac was too small for the included adaptor. Lint was sstaying out of the vent, just had to rake up the debris. Thoughtfully designed and complete package that anticipates various needs. Instructions are clear (read them!). materials made well. I particularly appreciate the (very literally) smallest item in the package: an extra set screw used to secure the brush to the rod.

Most amazing lint product ever, we burned up our dryer from build up and multiple passes with this thing even with a poorly constructed vent discharge by our unimpressive plumber didn't stop this thing.  24ft run with 3 bends and we got it completely cleaned and verified with a borescope camera.  AMAZING PRODUCT, bought the extensions with it also.

I had wet clothes at end of the cycle and also had overheat auto-shutdowns during a dry cycle. Once clean everything works like brand new again. I pulled out a file box worth of lint in the matter of 2 mins. Very impressed.

reviewText: Used it today to clean out dryer vent this tool works I had my doubts before I  Started  but after  seeing  all the lint that filled my shop vacuum  to its  limits  I was sold this is a great tool for any homeowner.

Brush cleans up vent very nicely after several passes and vacuum attached is a plus  Read instructions before using.  You don't want to have this stuck in vent.  One use and it already paid for itself.

reviewText: Followed other reviewers tips and taped the rods together, worked very well and I am pleased that the nasty task that my husband and I dread was not bad at all.  Now I don't worry about my dryer vent being a potential hazard, much cheaper to do yourself and on your schedule versus having a service company perform the work.

reviewText: Love this little gadget. never realized how much stuff gets embedded in the pipes leading outside the house. this thing eats it up. you'll save the money it cost in your powerbill the first month. follow the instructions and its easy.

It seems very difficult to make the rod with brush to turn 90 degree inside the pipe, and i had to disassemble the vent pipe.  Still highly recommend as it is simple and effective.

It does what it state, brought this Gardus RLE202 and Gardus R3203612 extension kit, clean vent from outside with dryer running, then remove dryer and clean it from the inside, used air blower from inside.  Now have a clean vent.

Just what I was looking for to clean the dryer vent, who knew haw much lint can get trapped in the vent line.  Easy to use and assemble, we have close to 18 feet on vent to go through and with the help of a shop vac worked great.

Additionally, since my dryer vent pipe is nearly 30 feet long and has weird curves inside the walls, I found that managing/handling that many extensions caused the poles to become twisted.

Though it was slipping with the drill, I just fed it by hand and was able to remove alot of lint.  My clothes dries much faster now. Great value. - housewife

A great tool the spinning provided by a drill and the brush bristle pattern this cleaning head cleans and navigates beyond expectations.

Worked better than expected.  Did eventually get the extension pack to help clear a 24' run of dryer vent.  Birds weren't too happy.  Shocked the previous owners didn't start a fire with as much debris that I cleaned out.

Extremely easy to use and quick to master.  Used this from inside the home rather than climb extension ladder to the exhaust vent near the roof.  Laundry is on the 2nd floor.  Shop-vac attachment worked well.

Nice piece of mind that I don't have this as a fire risk in my house.

I almost never write reviews, but had to this time.  I bought the lint lizard previously, and was very sleptical of this at first.  This product is amazing and you would not believe the amount of lint that came flying out of our dryer vent after this thing was shoved in there.  Very easy to use, but it did take two people, one to feed it in and one to operate the drill.

Worth every penny and saved us a $180 service call to have someone else clean the vent!  Pays for itself after one use.

No problems, works as advertised.  Removed 16 years of lint in around 10 minutes.  I filled up a large shop vac.  It is probably a once a year tool, but very handy.  My vent is 16 plus feet an I had no problems cleaning the vent by myself.  A 2nd person would have made it a little easier.

Easy to use - exceptionally effective! Flex in rods makes working around bends a piece of cake. Vacuum attachment fit perfectly. A little proactive use can add life to your dryer and avoid fire issues!

Execellent product. It took years of link from the dryer vent in a matter of minutes. I did need to use the optional extend rods to do the job. But it did a first class job. Dryer is working like it did new.

Was kind of expecting this to be somewhat cheap and probably break on me as my dryer duct is about 30ft long with various turns but it worked great no problems even with the extension kit. Got a good 3 gallons or more of lint out of my duct work, drying times went from 2hrs to 40 minutes, very happy now.

Gardus RLE202 LintEater 10-Piece Rotary Dryer Vent Cleaning System worked as advertised. I also purchased the extension pack as my vent goes out the roof and is over 20' long. it cleaned out my very long dryer vent tube.  I had to add an additional 4 sections of rod, and it did become cumbersome to handle, but if you take your time you can clean up to 20ft of tube!!!  I got a mountian of lint out and my dryer really pushes the air out now!

This was an excellent purchase from Amazon. Not only was the price best anywhere, the item was shipped extremely fast. The product was a breeze to use and mad emy dryer perform like new again. Excellent, and i would recommend thsi to anyone!!!

Following the easy instructions I was able to successfully clear our vent and save a trip from a pro. reviewText: You will need thermal tape and tin snips/industrial scissors for sure. It comes with screw claps that are good. Has curved section, by each hole on the inside, to smooth out exhaust flow. Measure, slide ends in or out, cut excess sheet metal, test fit. If it fits good then finish trimming excess metal and then cover ends with thermal tape.

I was having problems with my dryer not drying right so i researched and found this great item the air flow is way better than that slinky thing it had before i just wish i found out about this item sooner its the best thing you can buy for your dryer less drying time thats the biggest plus
summary: The best item you can buy for your dryer

reviewText: Like the headline says the product is superb, a great fit on my samsung dryer. The best thing about it is its slim design compared to a traditional vent.  The delivery is what killed it for me. I paid for this vent to be delivered next day because it was urgent that it arrived the day before or day of our install.  This item came late, 4 days late and I got no price adjustment or shipping refund.

Previously purchased the washer hoses sporting the movable elbow.  Great idea but they leaked at the elbow fittings.  Replaced with these hoses.  They are solidly built, do not leak at the connections, and appear engineered to withstand bursting concerns.

The best cleaning brush. Its so easy to clean under my appliances all cheerios and dust come out with one brush. It has a long handle and is flexible so it  goes in deep and also cleans the coils of under my fridge.

Not only do these hoses fit perfectly and are reassuringly solid feeling my Amazon order history gives me the date I purchased them so I know that in July of 2017 I need to replace them!!  Anyway since installing them no leaks and the washer fills up fine and all that.

Lasted one year then corroded and leaked. What ever metal they used for the threaded part is susceptible to rust quickly. Low quality metal coupled with a thin wall is a bad design. Too bad because the hoses are really nice quality. Swing and a miss on the metal ends.
summary: threaded connects corrode quickly. lasted one year then leaked

reviewText: The standard hoses offered at local hardware stores seem much cheaper than these quality ones AND with the price being about the same, these are worth it! They feel heavy duty as advertised and were easy to install.

This was a great improvement from that foil hose that we originally had. The way our fixture is in the apartment, I had to prop the dryer on blocks to get it high enough for the pieces to connect. This has worked as expected.

The Whirlpool Multi cleaning brush worked perfectly for my Kitchenaid refreigerator.  it had no problems reaching every coil and help me to pull a lot of pet hair and accumulation from the coils.  well made and strong handle.

reviewText:
This thing is junk!

Its super flimsy, and even with vent tape leaks air.  It looked like a great space saver, but in reality was a pain in the but to mesure, cut and install at the correct height.  Once installed and tested it leaked worse than a soaker hose.

Save your money, and stick with regular vent hose.  I think there is a reason why no brick and mortar store sells these.

Finally, a decent quality 90 degree fill hose connection for our washing machine!  It takes the stress off the hose connection.  Our previous straight hose leaked at the connection to the washer.  This one worked perfectly right out of the bos.

Needed a hose with a 90 degree turn so the hoses did not rub the wall, I purchased these guys and a spare for later. They worked perfectly, the old ones had a mark on the wall, these guys althouth still close had about a 1/4 gap, so if the machine starts a rockin i don't have to worry about my neighbor a knockin for a flood.

reviewText: Washer hoses arrived in time line advertised and were of the quality advertised. They have been connected to the wash machine and by all appearances are providing the service anticipated, although it is way to early to tell how they will hold up.  Overall, well satisfied with all aspects of the transaction.

sears delivered  and installed this dryer vent with no issues. The space where the washer and dryer only had 32" to clear the garage door and we knew the stand dryer vent hose kit would not work and this product wad perfect

reviewText: This is heads and shoulders above using solid copper pipes and ferrules and compression nuts and risking over tightening for us non-plumbers.  The construction appears very sturdy and it's super flexible.

Price is a little high but I think it was worth it, didn't want to cheap out the worst thing is come home to a flooded kitchen because of a failed hose.

My dryer needed a four-pronged cord after my old and terrible landlord switched the orignal out for a 3 pronged at our last residence...he didn't leave our original cord which was highly irritaiting and so this fit the dryer and at a MUCH CHEAPER cost than buying it in town at the hardware stores.

Great price for a great solid product. Liked the fact that it was a little longer length than what you find in most stores, allows for more wiggle room when adjusting the dryer. quality feels great, and would recommend it to anyone wanting a value oriented 4 wire power cord.

reviewText: I had to change my dryer from a 3 prong to this 4 prong cord.  I liked this product because I think the price was very reasonable for a 6ft cord.  The ends are clearly color coated so it mad the installation easy.

Product is the same as others I have purchased. Whether or not you replace them every 6 mos. as recommended I think depends upon your level of usage, i.e., number of people in family. I go around a year with mine before changing. When the water becomes too slow--that's when I change it.

This ridgid short sweep elbow solves the problem of kinking duct pipe. After I connect the remaining ductwork I should have a solution to my dryer venting problem - No more hot air blowing into the laundry room.

Worked perfectly - bought two of these as we have minimal space behind our W/D set and the flexible pipe kept getting smashed flat.  Now have flexible pipe between them so we can easily move either unit in or out and these plugged right in to the Dryer and wall connections no problem.

No leaks, item was well packaged, no damage like others stated. I do wonder about void spaces in the inner part of bend and lint buildup over time but would tend to believe a yearly cleanup would stop any problems from fully developing.

Would not hold dryer hose to exhaust fan inlet even when tightened all the way. These need to be able to be tightened down more for a secure fit. I'll go an get some worm screw clamps from the auto parts store that I can tighten down until tight.

reviewText: Lifesaver. Well not really but apparently gone are the days when one with even a modicum of skill could change their dryer form back- to side-exhaust. Not much to say here, arrived fast, great quality, and durability. Seems to be holding up to 500cfm which is impressive as the last product I had purchased from home depot could not stand that amount of air running through it. Would recommend.

no regrets.. will order again if I ever finally run out!

reviewText: Six months in the display started malfunctioning.  Amazon says return window closed 3 days after purchase.  Replaced batteries in sensor and main unit to no avail.  Worked great until it didn't anymore.

reviewText:
I bought this to replace a larger AcuRite I'd had for 5+ years (that units outdoor sensor failed.  This new one was ok for about 2 months (thought inside temps conflicted with AC thermostat.  Now the outside unit is reading temp and humidity incorrectly; despite careful (shielded from the weather) placement of the transmitter sensor.

Time to hunt down another brand.

Owned this thing for a week or so then, Once the temp outdoors dropped below freezing, this thing went wacky.  It began reporting insanely incorrect temps (158 deg F!) so I pulled the new batteries and did essentially a reset.  This fixed the problem for a day, then the same troubles.  This thing is useless as it only wants to function normally some of the time.  Poor QC by manufacturer on this one!  Now, off to find one that actually works as advertised.

I love it, perfect and you can wake up and get the correct weather and take it with you to any room. Careful do not put it around warm metals/ electronics, you won't get the correct numbers. reviewText: Installed it December 2015 in my house and still works great in May, 2016. Low battery light came on, but still functioning, so expect at least 6 months out of the battery. AcuWhat????. Followed directions exactly and used fresh batteries.  Worked OK for 1 day.  Second day outside humidity went to 1% on display and stayed in single digits even though actual humidity over 20%.  Note sensor installed under an eave with no sun and good air flow exactly according to instructions.  Will probably just throw this useless thing in trash and go back to Google weather..

reviewText: We bought this after searching other sites that charged a times this much for the exact same heating element.  It is working perfectly so far.  Would definitely recommend trying Amazon.com first before paying much higher prices somewhere else.

Received this motor promptly from Pandoras OEM Appliance parts and it was an OEM part as listed.  Electrical terminals were color coded to match the corresponding wires for hookup.  My '91 dryer is running like new again.  Going to purchase more parts from Pandora to give the matching washing machine a tune-up.

Item arrived on time and did a great job.  It makes ice faster than the one Sears tried to force me to buy.  Returned the Sears ice maker and purchased this one and am completely satisified with the results and performance.  By to Sears.

Delivered promptly and as advertised.  Had some issues because the color coding was opposite of the unit I was replacing (not  a direct replacement) and the fan spun backwards, but that was easily switched.

Installed in 10 minutes on my kitchaid superba side by side. Only step aside from install was to remove the cables from the OEM ice-maker and move to the replacement. Everything lined up perfectly. Bye bye OEM maker and bye bye paint chips in my ice!

reviewText: After looking at the cost of the motors from Sears Parts Direct I decided to do some searching. I found this and completely satisfied with the seller for the description and shipping of the motor. It came with the pulley as some do not, so definitely would purchase again.

Motor 279787 is not the same as 3395654 the wiring is different,mine came with no instructions,You cant just call this company Seneca River Trading, they don't answer their phone and are difficult to contact. Save yourself the time and frustration and spend more for the exact replacement,its worth it.

The mounting bracket has to be filed to fit, the wires were to short and finally the when running the fan blows out instead of in to exhaust the stove. Will have to take it apart to reverse the fan blade.

It was difficult to get the thing on. We did manage to get it on.  You need strong fingers of steel or some tool you can hold that retaining clip without pinching your fingers.  I am very happy though because it solved the leak which solved are floor from bowing.

Knob was received earlier than expected and the shipping container protected the item very well.  Color matched the defective original part and fit on mechanical timer shaft as required. This knob has retained the original look on this appliance making the users very satisfied. Supplier will be used in future for these difficult to find parts.

This dryer vent screen is an exact fit....Now my vent on the dryer will clog up .with lint...The price from Amazon was great...shipping was very fast..Note:  other sources for this item was more money..Amazon always is the better choice for shopping...works for me....Jp , Sharon MA.
summary: Screen for Clothes Dryer found Here

reviewText: Glad to find this replacement online.  I was looking for one to replace my broken filter for the Kenmore model.  If I get it from sears part it'll be more than double.  I have look up from internet to know it will fit for my Kenmore dryer, that sure save me some money.
summary: A good replacement for my broken one

reviewText: Too small. Bought package of 5 for $8.00 from local appliance store. All too small. Reordered using serial number and model number of Maytag Gemini stove, also undersized, however only $4.00 for one. Every evaluation posted in Amazon product description states "undersized" as main complaint. How come manufacturer does not make correction?

These worked fantastic they worked perfectly on my Frigidaire Gallery burner grades...No more rocking only a couple were missing so I didn't want to buy the entire kit..So I bought these and some Permatex Gasket Silicone and that did the trick..was an easy fix and installed without any issues...

reviewText: This is the recommended one for my fridge and it did not snap in all the way.  Could be my fridge but I doubt it.  1 star based off my frustration.  It would not click in but once it did and I hit the water, it fired out like a tomahawk cruise missle

Came in good time but needed to be packed better, side broken and tube of alumlatics had damaged side also , when you squeezed tube it came out in your hand . Amazon agree to take care of it but I took a part off ole one to get it installed , A big job and I don't want to take back out , would be nice to get something off for trouble, but I'll live with it.

reviewText: The bulb in our older Magic Chef microwave recently burnt out and was unavailable. Ordered this replacement bulb that seemed to compare in every aspect as far as I could see with the available internet pictures and specs to the original bulb. Well, after installing it, this turned out to be the part that I needed and it works just like new again and at a reasonable cost. Unfortunately we jumped ahead of ourselves and bought another oven on sale @ BB but will keep this as a backup unit for future needs.
summary: Quality part saved an otherwise excellent appliance ..

reviewText: After blowing our budget on the commercial six burner range we decided to buy a cheap alternative. We were pleasantly surprised with the quality and over all look. Gave our the kitchen the commercial look we were after. Works very well.
summary: Great industrial look for a great price.

reviewText: An absolute $#$@!#$#$ to install but that was due to vent alignment issues beyond the control of the manufacturer. We ordered ours from Warehouse deals, it arrived with a small dent in the front. The two speed van was an unexpected bonus. Unit is now installed and working well.

reviewText: Better than any found at Home Depot or lowes,,and they are very hard to find there ,,usually hidden in the back somewhere,,,just what I needed,,and I found and ordered the charcoal filters here as well...yea,,shipped straight to the door and no searching in cold rainy weather...

I bought this wall cap and one from Broan at the same time for two projects around my home.  Nutone is a superior product.  The metal is thicker, the mesh wire doesn't come off, there pipe that comes off the back of the unit and there are six holes surrounding the device that make installation a snap and also makes the device tight and secure.

Pros:
Well built
6 installation holes
Permanent Mesh

Con:
2 small holes in the inner tubing that were easily covered with installation tape.

Don't waste your $ on cheap plastic covers.  I bought these at Menards for $9.99 -- not sure why so much higher at other places.  Anyway, heavy gauge steel, epoxy painted, dampered cover (no noise!), and spring tension (no flapping in the wind).  Screen to keep out critters.  These will last forever, unlike the plastic ones that rot-out, are noisy, and birds get through.

I looked on line every where. I found the identical part being sold at sears for $100.00 more, plus i would have to pay sales tax. I was sort of weary about buying this magnatron, but decided to make the purchase since i have had great luck with other Amazon items. When installing the item, i quickly wound out that the magnets were much stronger than the one i took out. The item fixed my microwave oven, and i saved a ton of money.

Not much to say- replacement unit fits perfectly and functions like new.  Added bonus was inclusion of various wiring harnesses to fit multiple brands and good instructions.  Unit was purchased for a Sub-Zero model 590.  Fast, safe shipping from vendor a plus.

Miss my thermador alot!!! Sold my custom home(I built myselfin in 2004) w/sgsx36 in it. Moved into the spec house (I built next door)W/ a Jen-Air, Big mistake. Am going to trash the Jen-air & get another Thermador!

This washer is very noisy & was a problem from the start.  Auto load sensing has a mind of its own. Machine will start wash cycle totally dry then sprays water on spin cycle so clothes are soaked when washer stops.

I bought these to flush out my tankless water heater. Hooked them up to the pump I also purchased on Amazon, and had no issues whatsoever. Job well done, 150 bucks saved and they are still good for future use

reviewText:
Perfect length, flexible, no leaks when installed.  Fit perfectly from wall box water service to back of Whirpool washer.

Manufacture says to replace these at least every 5 years.  These are inexpensive enough to keep spares on hand.

Fit my Samsung microwave perfectly and looked exactly like the part I replaced.  It was very easy to install.  YouTube has great videos on how to do it.  This did not come with the spring, so if that broke as well, you will have to order that separately .

Now, this is a Cooker. Installed well, and works great. Put it in place of an inadequate electric one, and only had to do a little trimming. Mounted easily. I did have to use a compression washer included, on the inlet fitting. Nothing about that in the instructions, that I found.

we have electric stove, but I wanted a backup with natural gas as we have some situation where we were out of electricity after some storm. Looks and feels good. we often use it more often than I initially thought

Item broke under 3 yrs. LG admitted to having a problem with this series , the pump goes out. They also have a service bulletin that states replace the control board as well. So here we are at 35 months and I get an estimate of $600 to repair because LG is reviewing y case to see if they will extend my warranty based on the issues they have had. Therefore stay away from this model

Installation took about 2 min. Unit works great. Replaced griddle/ grill to make 4 burner stove. there are 2 different plug styles for these cartridge units. look to confirm the plug type of your base before ordering a cartridge.

I love this radiant range cartridge- worked perfectly in my 25 year old Jenn Air range (model s- 136) The dimensions were not correctly displayed on the web site which made me hesitant to buy. The glass top is actually approx. 11" x 19 ". I knew the plug ins and the wattage was right - so took a chance. It is easy to clean with windex  or any type of glass cleaner. MY old cartridge died and this was a nice upgrade for me.

reviewText: The JennAire panel met all my requirements.  My unit is ten years old and it is hard to find replacements.  Expecially at a resonable price. My husband tried another supplier.  They sent the wrong one and charged us 20percent restocking fee.  Amazon and their suppliers are the best.

This seal was the best price on the internet. I needed it to replace the old leaking seal on my split outer tub Samsung front load washer. Repair was difficult but part easy to install once the tub was taken out of the unit.

Bought the tray and re installed sensor..The sensor wire had broken from former use and ice water froze and old tray wouldnt make cubes but produce a large block of ice which broke the tray. I had to splice the broken wire from the sensor. After wire was repaired new tray produced ice cubes. Tray fit correctly and functions as designed now. Lots of ice cubes now.

I bought 2 of these. One for hot and one for cold for LG washing machine front loader. Couldn't find a long enough one before, they were all 4 ft at my local home depot. This was the perfect solution and needed a braided one in lieu of my rubber ones that were spliced together before and leaking. Seems strong and hopefully last long

reviewText: I use this to vent the different circuits in our home baseboard radiation heating system.  Works like a charm; only took me thirty years to figure out.  YouTube has a video on how to do it.  The metal sheathing is needed with the hot water.

reviewText: Arrived on time, so far after 3 loads, have worked perfectly.  I was unable to find a washing machine hose this long anywhere else including teh big box stores and a local plumbing specialty store, so was thrilled to find it.

reviewText: No, complaints with this tube.  I got it to connect my Washing Machine to the Dryer so I could use the steam function.  This cord is plenty long, I can now move my dryer without moving the washing machine too.  I have a lot of extra slack which hides nicely behind the machine.

reviewText: Was pleaseatly surprised at the quality of these. I am one to be a little skepical about product descriptions written by the seller but this one exceeds expectations. A good solid product. Extra length a nice plus as well.

reviewText:

Shipping speed could of been better than a week but it wasn't Prime, and it was free. So that's that.

Was perfect! Exactly what we needed. Everything worked fine on our dry. The lights lit up and we were able to choose our cycle but when we went to push start, nothing happened. A Google search said our thermal fuse might have blown. This is what else were hoping for since it is the cheapest fix. But we never took apart our dryer before. Thank goodness for YouTube. Took 5 min to put in and saved us $200-$300 for Sears to come out.

We have the Samsung dryer model dv331awe/xaa

Perfect replacement and restored my microwave to operation.  It wasn't to bad an installation.  Check on youtube for methods you'll find there to place a brace on the steel bracket that bent in the first place and caused the breakage, (the popsicle stick fix) .

So disappointed that 4 weeks after installation, this product stopped working.  Had to pay a repair person second time and they indicated that they routinely see this 4-6 weeks after installation with parts purchased on Amazon.  Probably the first Amazon-fail we have had with any product.

It fit without issues or modifications which was a relief. Used it on a Samsung front load dryer.  It gets real hot and therefore dries clothes like you would expect ;)  I would purchase again if the elements failed in several years from now.

reviewText: so far so good.  if it fails early, will re-order but  treat it like a halogen bulb... no hand oils/handle with gloves.  Checked with ohm meter to make sure element wasn't getting contact with the metal plate that it is set up on.

Some videos  show more work than necessary  so watch more than one. Took me about  half hour to swap out. Be sure to throw the breaker or unplug  dryer for safety before replacing.

I do really like the Air-O-Swiss humidifier and together the components don't produce much if at all white dust and I believe the demineral helps - as I'm not about to buy distilled water living in NYC nor do I want to really use up my water filter, so I get this.

reviewText:
I had earlier read a review of a customer that stated that you should always buy the filled cartridge be cause the refills were a mess.
I decided to try my luck.
The process was straigt forward.
Will buy again when this ine runs out.

My fridge had water and ice under crisper drawer. After a search on YouTube I found the solution and ordered this part. My Samsung French door bottom freezer is now thawing and draining as it should. Not bad for a 57 year old handy woman. LOL Great product, fast shipping, and followed up after the sale.

When our dryer suddenly stopped working, it had a huge impact.  This belt was inexpensive, arrived ahead of schedule and fit our Samsung Dryer model DV520AGP.  The repair steps are available online, required minimal tools and the dryer is back to normal.

Did not fit my Samsung model # DV219AGW/XAA.  This belt is just a bit too short and made the idler pulley wheel rub up against the motor housing after Installation. Nasty smell. You get what you pay for.

Be very careful with these belts! They are longer & wider than the belt should be & cost me the use of my dryer for additional days until my belts arrived from Samsung. I would not recommend ordering from here!

The roller bushing sleeve wore out, therefore causing the belt to begin to slip. The price for the belt was competitive, where the true savings came in the total cost of part and shipping...added up to be less than with other vendors outside Amazon.

This is better than the original belt in build and quality. Price is 25% of retail and is great for a do it yourself repair family on a budget. Questions?, ask a question at this review including the model number, I will guide you as to the best part.

this belt gets eaten by the drier a lot  like every couple years. so this time I bought 4.  at less than $2 a piece I am set for a while.  eventually I will be able to change this belt without having to remember which screw goes where, because you have to take almost the entire front if the drier apart to change it.  all phillips head screws so it is pretty easy, just build a screw map.

Have table over vent and was getting a blast of cold air right up the side of my chair, then I put the extend a vent over the vent and moved the air to the front of the table and into the room for all to get the benefit of the air conditioner. Works great.
summary: Must have if vent is under table or couch

reviewText: Looked good in the description. I should have read the details and reviews. Firstly, it is too small in width for many US registers. This product only spanned about 80% of our register. (About 13 inches). Secondly our new furnace literally lifted the light weight plastic off the floor. Only If you have narrow registers And your airflow is slow this might be a good choice.

Great item and solid material. Unlike other reviews of similiar items and reviews which many stated cheaply made material that warps. item by Range Kleen is of high quality and solid material that doesn't warp whatsoever. Fit range perfectly and easy to clean from grease etc., Highly recommend range kleen product and is reasonably priced.

Best one out there. I owned 4, this one takes the cake.  Classy design and great functionality.  Will actually freeze water bottles in the bottom if you turn it down too low.  Of course this is unlock most of these things the give you pee warm drinks.  This is well made.  Only complaint is if it's not in a cabinet , you can hear it kick on and off, not annoyingly but it's noticeable.

Got this as a birthday present and used it almost daily. It looks awesome, kept everything plenty cold (beer/energy drinks), but one day I noticed that it wasn't getting cold and making a straining electrical humming sound and then clicking a relay off.

First thing i did was come to amazon and BOOM 31 reviews mostly like my own experience. Have yet to try and contact edgestar since it seems like its a did end i might go straight to the better business bureau. Ill update the review if i go ahead with it.

reviewText: We love this stuff!  So much healthier than G*torade!  Often it is cheaper at our local outdoors store but Prime makes is very convenient.  My husband drinks it after working in the yard, on projects, hiking, running - really anytime he exercises or is outdoors.  I can also attest to it's effectiveness of rebalancing your electrolytes!

OK, I'll pile on here.  A few days into my citrus flavor. Yum.  Free of sugary sweet and lab grown poisons,
nice for daily use pre/post walkercise, and not a bad item to have for emergencies either. I got
my 2.2# bulk tub elsewhere because this listing doesn't give its weight, and, you might have noticed,

Powerful blower and works to remove smoke from searing steaks.  No worries here in setting off the fire alarm again!  Loud but expected with this level of CFMs  Pleased with purchase and Amazon delivered it quickly and on time.

Great replacement for the original silverware basket that came with my Kenmore Elite dishwasher.  Seems very sturdy and fits perfectly.  More reasonably priced than the one on Sears replacement parts website.

Appears to be better built than original but perhaps the old one was ravaged by time. The small grids kept breaking & the silverware would stick out the basket bottom.  About 1/2 the cost of manufacturer's site.  Great value

The basket That came with my dishwasher starting breaking on the bottom with in a few years, silverware could fall right through. Glad to get a new one, alittle pricey but worth it so silverware doesn't slide through

Awesome unit

-helped me see which rooms need air circulation due to high CO2, the levels in some of these rooms reached 3000.  Circulating the area got the room back down to 400/500 and everyone is breathing easier!

Thanks

I didn't want to drop over 100 bucks but needed accuracy, this has big time instant change in ppm level monitoring co2 is nice to have. Makes it easy to dial in regulator with it's precision. No batteries. Sucks for mounting though....no holes....just give it a nice seat to sit on. It's nice.

taking it out of the box it said my room had over 2500 ppm of co2 which had to be wrong but after i took it outside and got it in fresh air it read inside my rooms correctly.  great piece of gear for my indoor grow room.

We thought our electronics had gone out because our oven would not cut off. Priced this part locally and it was close to $60.00. Got it on Amazon for 1/3 of that and the new element solved our problem.
summary: We thought our electronics had gone out because our oven ...

reviewText:
This part fits old whirlpool ranges, mine is 1987 vintage.
If your broiler (upper) coil is working, the problem is probably the lower coil. If possible be sure you have 240 volts at the leads. Be very careful when you test, as it is a lot of voltage.
 Check out ehow or youtube for hints on how to do this.
My frozen pizza came out perfect, YUM.
John

Works great. Easy to install. Price was the best part, so low I was afraid of what I would get but its perfect. I highly recommend this seller to everyone, fast quick shipping  I'll definitely be a repeat customer.

Was delivered on time connected easily and works as it should. I installed then set the oven on 400 and let the element burn off any residue that may hay been on it. I don't use the oven very often but the element is working just fine when I do.

Just before Christmas our oven element died. Local parts place had it for $99, ...ouch. (Would have been $30 is I was a contractors, ...but that is another story). Ordered from amazon instead, was $15 including shipping, came in 3 days, eazy installation and worked perfect.

I erred in ordering this which was too wide for my Kenmore 911. While awaiting the correct one (GE WB44K5013) I squeezed it inwards and it bent enough to fit! Works like a charm. I'm keeping the GE as a spare - since my original lasted at least 12 years I may never need it.

This product works as designed.  I use the vinyl for venting a bathroom fan.  I stay away from the foil type because they'll eventually rot out from the moisture.

Be careful not to tear it when installing.  either on nails from a subfloor or on the aluminum collars that sometimes have a sharp edge sticking out.

to bad none of the box stores carry vinyl ducts; not sure why.

I got this because I didn't want to pay more for the aluminium duct just to vent bathroom fan. This serves nicely. It does have some nasty plastic smell when new, but I'm running this through the attic and after time the smell goes away.

Airtight is the way to go This kit was absolutely perfect, and is performing better than expected. Also suggest as other reviewers did to get the bonding cement Only $6.95 from Amazon, and made all the difference for the best deal possible.

First home with a whole house humidifier, OMG this is so nice vs the fill and refill and replace filters in a stand up humidifier!  Filters last me about 2 months with well water use, very happy reorder all the time as needed.
summary: Very nice filter, i get about 2 months of them with well water so easy to change as well, very happy :)

reviewText: Filter fits and works great if you have the humidifier this works with. However I'd recommend not to get a drum style humidifier like this I have not seen much over 10% increase in humidity I know it is due to leaky home but still the chunking up from the minerals in the water as well but anyway filter works as supposed to

Lower price that I have come across in the big box stores.  Works well as long as changed twice/season.  I live in cold climate, also fairly hard well water, which loads up the pad with minerals quickly.

I ordered these and received them very quickly.  My only complaint is NOT with these items, but with my carelessness.  In replacing the old pad I did not seat it carefully and thoroughly.  I got a wet floor out of it!  My bad.  These are fine, and work well with my furnace Aprilairre humidifier.

I have a 400 cigar humidor. This is a little big for that but im not complaining.  Makes a massive differance.  Now that the cigars are correctly humidified they smike like the ones from the cigar shops.

This was the second one I have used stainless backsplash from cooktop to microwave.  Always pleased with the look and ease of maintenance.  Compliments the linear glass tile with stainless accent tiles.
summary: Value and looks in back splash.

reviewText: Not flimsy, protective covering and well packaged.  We used it as our back splash behind the stainless range then mounted the 30" Over Range Shelf Extra Deep 3.5"( Stainless Steel) also purchased here on Amazon.  Looks like they were made to go together....  Very attractive.

reviewText: Well worth the price.  Just bought two sets for our new front loaders just installed.  We have a second floor laundry and its just amazing how well these work.  I can hardly tell the that machines are running from downstairs even when on the spin cycle.

Product is very easy to install.  I liked that it comes with pre-teflon taped fitting.  All parts needed included. Have done so far 20 loads of dishes on same cartidge insert.  Installed like just behind cabinet doors behind center post and did not need mounting bracket.  If you have hard water...a much needed product if you do not want a whole house water softener system.

Where he plays with the original ones they seem to fit perfectly but after several uses I cook several times that was like an electricity electrical charge coming off of it and what was happening where the little curve is it was touching the main plug I had to actually use the special high temperature glue to protect the wire

reviewText: These fit my 10+ year old GE stove perfectly. I had gone to Lowe's and got the standard 8 inch and 6 inch covers and they were too small. These look great and are exactly what I needed, thank you! and i saved $4 buyinig off Amazon vs Lowes.

dont waste your money. Fitment doesn't exist, {they were cut to wrong specifications} they are also 1/2 inch diameter shorter that OEM which means they don't cover as trim prices. Because the slots are cut wrong the burner does not fit flush in stove.

If they hold up nicely in the future, they were a perfect choice to spuce up the trusty rusty old dull burnt SS discs.  A no-brainer--wish I would have purchased much sooner.  Make the white GE look clean and slick in my old condo.  Try them if you're on the fence!

In the dishwasher. Save time and money and just buy them. We I move they are coming with me.

reviewText: I have below the shoulder medium thick hair.  I am very pleased with this product. It works best if I use my regular dryer until my hair semi dry (just finger dry). Good results in under 5 minutes.  Let hair cool before brushing to set.  The spin feature takes a little practice.

reviewText: I love this Conair + I have a cabinet of their dryers & flat irons. My hair has become fragile when exposed to dryer heat. It appears stylish, then within the hour- poof! It expands out. Not attractive version of myself. This device has given me soft, lustrous, curled hair, again. Brilliant product design! Thank-you much.

Love this product. This is my second purchase because I wanted one to stay home and have one in my travel bag! I have baby fine hair and when used in combination with a little root product, I get the volume I need. Love the spin action especially since "coordination" is not my middle name. Would highly recommend!

super fat brush.  can use spin or not works great to style hair from wet to dry.  Makes hair smooth and soft.  I was unsure when I ordered so glad I took a chance.  I often use only this to style my hair no other straightener or curler needed.

Great dryer & styler - I have fine hair just below my ears and its easy and quick to use.  Keeps my hair shiny and frizz free with some body.  I would like to keep bounce and body for the day and wondering what serum to use with this styler and also how to wash the brush head?

reviewText: Love this. Leaves hair silky and bouncy and with lots of volume. I use it with the styling serum (had several different types - all work). My hair is shoulder length and chemically treated , therefore are coarse and untamed. This tames them

reviewText: Arrived as described and within the predicted delivery time. They were a perfect fit and heat faster and hotter than my old elements. I believe this product is a good value for the price. I replaced all the heating elements and my 5 year old stove top works like new.

Very well made product, looks exactly like those from Lowes etc but less than 1/2 the price, worked fine on my 30 year old GE stove, but note I had to also change the receptor as well because the prongs were about 3/8 inch shorter than the old one

These 6 inch replacements have been on my stove for a few weeks now and they work great i would recommend these to anyone looking to revive your GE stove. Make sure your connections and wires are in good shape before installing. Amazon sells the wiring harnesses.

We got it installed it easily and it worked right away cooling the internals. I couldn't understand how this would help the hot panel on the other side of the fridge but I don't need to it worked great! Easy install get the fan blade! You must...

I was afraid about the installation process after watching a video in the YouTube that suggested a need to unscrew the old motor.  But the Samsung refrigerator Condenser Fan system is very simple and completely screw-less. It is a snap on system and it took me  2 minutes to take out the old unit and install the new one.

I do agree with the other reviewer: order the Fan Assembly Da31-00010c and install it together.

Good Luck!

I troubleshoot my neighbors refrigerator noise to the condenser fan bearings going bad after several years. I found this assembly much cheaper through Amazon than any local store. I ordered it from Samsung Parts and it arrived within days (thank you Prime!). I swapped the fan out in a few minutes and my neighbor is extremely happy.

I have a Samsung RS3520BBP side by side fridge that I installed this on. It fit perfect and solved the noise issue. I would by a new fan blade (DA31-00010C) with this as the old motor/fan combo are locktited togther.
summary: Replaced a noisy fan motor with this new one

reviewText: This icemaker works perfectly! Have a newer frigidaire refrigerator and the icemaker stopped working! Frigidaire and lowes were complete douchebags, and rather than argue about an icemaker I purchased this unit. Easy installation and lotsa ice! Love it!

Good price!  It is a spare to replace prior spare that I had to use.  That motor is critical.  Runs continuously.  Lasts many years, but will quit at very inopportune times!  New one tested and put away!

We are very happy with this stainless hood. Now I took a day and a half to install it but that's because I took my time and did it right. I did run into a noise problem on high but all that was is a loose hub which tightened up with a couple twists and it is quiet as can be now. It is a handsome addition to any kitchen and will look great with our new stainless Kitchenaid range. This is a great buy.
summary: Why pay a 1,000 dollars when this one is just premo.

reviewText: Beautiful hood , if your ceiling is more than 8ft tall you'll have to order extra chimney sections , they have a great web site , also if your not going to vent it you'll need to order the recirculating filter
summary: Beautiful hood, if your ceiling is more than 8ft ...

reviewText: Failed after less then a few uses.  I have a double convection oven and thought possible the oven was at fault since this item was very new.  I tried it in the other oven and again failed.  I tried the original one which was working but starting to come apart and it worked fine.  Try another brand or stick with the original one.
summary: Failed shortly after purchase.  Do not recommend.

reviewText: This Temp Probe has a different tip than the OEM probe but its works as advertised on my 2016 Electrolux Induction range.  We have used it to cook both beef and poultry and the temperature reading is accurate.

When my meat probe bit the dust I checked out the replacemrnt Bosch part.  It was around $50 or more.
I found these on Amazon for a fraction of the price.  I bought two.  They seen to last about 8-9 years.
It works with the oven perfectly, just like the original. A def 5-star rating!

Purchased this replacement meat probe for my GE profile model number JK955S0K4SS oven and it worked perfectly! We were quite happy to find this worked instead of having to purchase the OEM model which was much more expensive!

I ordered this to use with a Whirlpool range, and it fit perfectly, just like advertised. It said it was universal, and i think it would work for any standard American 4 wire range. The directions were comprehensive, though they required a few reads, and the product felt really solid.
summary: Great universal cord for a Whirlpool oven

reviewText: Item worked for my GE Artistry range with some minor modifications to the back panel of my range.  This was not an issue with the cord, it is an issue with the design of the range.  I installed this cord by myself, and I have no electrical experience.

Did not need the Neutral (white) wire in my application (L2 EVSE), so I just cut it off where it exited the jacket.  Good quality pigtail cord and the length (4') is just right for almost any 240Vac power application.
summary: Worked great for L2 EVSE charging station application

reviewText:
excellent product to update a functional outdated older dishwasher .
Custom fitting measurements made update easy and simple.
Panels complement the stainless steel finish of my new appliances nicely.
I hope these last several years as I find the newer dishwashers exceedingly slow and hard to load.
summary: Excellent for updating an older dishwasher

reviewText: I purchased a two different Samsung filter models for a couple of Samsung refrigerators where I had installed HD HDX filters.  The HDX filters produced, best as I can describe, a chemical or plastic taste and odor.  The Samsung replacements do not have this problem.  I noticed the amazon product description states China.  Both models I purchased are made in Mexico.

Product was a perfect fit in my refrigerator and a snap to install.  No problem with attaching to the refrigerator bracket.  Water tests almost pure.  Recommend this product for any refrigerator it may fit.

Doesn't fit my Samsung refrigerator (model RF267ABPN), despite the filter being on the compatible list. The difference is in the molded pattern on the insert extension. I've posted an image of the model tag affixed inside my fridge, on the left wall, middle front.
summary: Doesn't fit Samsung refrigerator model RF267ABPN

reviewText: Went thru the exacto knife process on the leading edge of the primary tooth on both sides of the circular track.  bit painful. but it worked.  price of having NSF42/53/401 peace of mind but i wonder if it's worth it.
summary: Painful alteration to get filter to fit

reviewText: As indicated on this Amazon description, this product is NOT compatible with Samsung fridge that uses DA29-00003F. I am sure this product is fine for the correct fridge, but do not believe the description.
summary: I am sure this product is fine for the correct fridge

reviewText: Despite its claim this filter did not fit our Samsung refrigerator Model RS-265LABP; water element DA29-00003B.  We will be returning these filters ASAP.  The idea of not being able to get a replacement filter will have a strong influence on the next refrigerator we purchase and it probably won't be Samsung.

These did not fit. The p/n shows to be correct but the twist lock is not the same on the ones I received, therefore it would not lock into place. Returned and bought a no name filter that fit perfectly.

so I spent more to get a so called official Samsung filter and like so many others it does not fit. it will go in but impossible to turn. the teeth fittings are not the same as before. returning for refund. RIPOFF.

Samsung must have changed the design of the water filter receptacle because these went in no problem unlike some of the other reviews on here. I have however, got other filters on here that needed modification to go in. Either way it better than paying samsung 50 bucks for one filter
summary: Fit my samsung counter depth fridge

reviewText: Fits perfect on my Samsung side by side fridge. Why shouldn't it, after all it is a Samsung product. I was concerned with the picture on the box being a blank filter but inside the box was the stock filter with label indicating such. I bought 3 filters for about .50 cents cheaper than 2, go figure.

Easy to install and works fine. I have replaced these several times when the light goes on in my Samsung refrigerator. Never had a problem except for the price which seems excessive for a simple filter.
summary: Good replacement filter. Have used several times.

reviewText: This water filter is the same one that I was buying at a local store for a bunch more money.  These work great in my Samsung refrigerator and enjoy have water that tastes great coming out of my fridge.

These have been discontinued but still able to find them here on Amazon via various sellers. The new replacement are series "F" but I read of inferior particle category than series "G". I guess Samsung will always find ways to make money on everything even if it comes by lowering quality and jacking up prices on new "F" series.

We had already checked with Sears and got the 'run-a-round', ie. shifted to several depts. & then to Samsung itself and the price they each were finally able to offer was MUCH more than this price. Have already installed ne of the filters. Seems to be working just fine. Thanks.

Best Buy where I purchased my samsung refridgerator , I was buying my replacement filters there as well. On my last visit they were out of stock so I checked amazon & found that by buying the 3 pack I saved money & won't need to be concerned about stock being available.

...you don't have many choices about what water filter to use. I use these filters in a Samsung RFG237AARS refrigerator. Each one is in place for four to five months before the filter change indicator light appears. Easy install and perfect fit.

Could not find it cheaper anywhere.  Got to get the 3 pack they are only good for 6 months recommended.  Easy installinsert twist and lock.  Depending on your model.reset filter change prompt.  Most models  hold button down 3 seconds till clear.

Exactly as advertised - easier than having to go to the local home improvement store to purchase and spent less money - With Prime account there is not shipping so much easier to replace plus it was less expensive!!

Very nice filter, we are on a well w/ good water, just a little hard, but the filter lasts for several months. Installation on our frig is a little difficult, and if filter is not well set in housing a lot if water will spill out.

The real filters since 2008. Ships fast and never had any problems. Tried off brand a couple of times and was not as happy with them. I feel as others these are not cheap but I fell they are worth it for drinking water

Although I double checked the filter number, this particular filter didn't fit my Samsung counter depth refrigerator. I had to order another brand.  It says Samsung in description, but I don't think this filter is made by Samsung.  However, AMAZON made returns super easy.  Thanks so much!

I have bought several of these filters for my Samsung fridge and they last approx. 5 months before the replace filter light comes on. They are very easy to replace and filters very well. Best price is to get the two pack.
summary: Great filter and very easy to install.

reviewText: Have the Samsung refrigerator so this is the one to use....have ordered a cheaper brand to try, but have not used it yet...my daughter was happy with the lesser brand.  Your price is what made me order this because at the store it is more.

Home Depot carried their own brand filter not Aqua Pure which was the original filter that came with the purchase of the refrigerator.  It was a few dollars cheaper but I read reviews on Amazon saying it had a bad fit.  I bought this online and it is working fine.

We use these filters for the water system in our Samsung refrigerator (26 cubic ft). They work as they should and easy to replace. No issues. We're on our 2nd set...I buy them 2 at a time and currently using the 4th replacement filter. The order arrived on time. No drama.

I ran my last filter down to the Red light on my refridgerator just to see if I could tell a difference, and YES I could. It has more of a crisp taste and much cleaner feeling with no after taste. I would highly recommend buying here and not at Sears, I bought 2 for the price of one!!

I have purchased these filters sold by Amazon and I have been perfectly happy with them.  With Amazon Prime, delivery is in two days in my areas (Central Jersey), product is original Samsung (not some other OEM), and they work perfectly well and cheaper than buying in store.
summary: Filters are Samsung branded, work fine, prompt delivery

reviewText:
I use to be all about saving money on replacement parts for various appliances by getting after market products. After a few problems of leaking and not so clean water. I made sure that the next refrigerator I got I would only use the official filter from the manufacture.

This product works perfectly and the price and hassle free shipping through Amazon makes it a no-brainer to make sure you purchase via Amazon.
summary: Great price, official Samsung Filter Package

reviewText: Bought into the French Door refrigerator craze.  With that comes the requirement to replace the water filter every six months/300 gallons of water use, whichever comes first.  Found Amazon offered the filters in a multi-pack, and cheaper that all other sellers.  Recommend to everyone who bought a Samsung.

I love my new dishwasher. I couldn't install it with quick connection because I have nonstandart sink. I bought a water hose and installed it directly to hot water under my sink. Drain hose with weight is hanging to the sink. The dishwasher works great, but a little bit loudy, like laundry.
Good solid product, very quiet to. Dishes come out spotless. SPT Countertop Dishwasher, Silver

I waited a couple weeks to rate this item. I wanted to see how it would do. I was pretty surprised worked great. I liked that you can remove parts of the rack and move around silverware basket. I haven't seen the power bill yet so cross your fingers. Update five months later still going strong. It developed a squeak when the jet head spins but didn't impare anything. I think it might be wear or just plastic rubbing.

After having this unit it was amazing, Now I wish I never bought it. It has been leaking water from one of the 2 little holes on the bottom.  Now the place I rent they will have to replace the entire counter top. I did have this for almost 2 years and who knows how long its been leaking but still. be worry of it.
summary: After having this unit it was amazing, Now I wish I never bought it

reviewText: I got mine at walmart. Im in a wheelchair and im very small i had my kitchen cut down to 18 inch high cabinets and this fits right under it i ran it out its own drain. you can only see the top of the dishwasher in the photo to the right. I have been using it for 2 years and it works perfect

amazing - i've had it for 3 years and zero problems - i should have bought this YEARS before that - i use it for my apartment in nyc - it's been a huge timesaver - it EASILY out performs my top-line full size one at our vacation home that cost 3x this - solid build - easy load - well laid out interior - if it broke tomorrow there would be no hesitation to get another that day

Loved this when I first received it. However now that I have been using it for 5 months it us having problems. The lights are not working unless you bang on the door. Can't see to select cycle, can't tell if it is on or off.  Tried to conact company about warranty repair and have got zero response. If I have to replace will not be buying this brand again. Very very disappointed.

My cooktop broke Sunday night.....Placed an order for this one that night and this one came in Tues mid afternoon.
Was just like specs showed....easy set up took about 10 minutes to replace our old one.
It is prettier in person than in this picture.

After months being installed I finally got to use it. Both burners fired up, put a big pot to fried some battered gator tails. In no time the oil was hot to start frying.  No more smelling up the house when I can do the frying in my outdoor kitchen now.

I put 5 start because it did the job as I want it, it was hard to find out how the old belt was assemble, but after 30 min, I found the right track for the belt.

It is hard due to space constrains in dryiers but, be patient.

It is easy, drying is working just for less than 10usd, that's great, I save couple of hundred dollars.

Sure beats the prices I was seeing online,  came fast and in factory package.  Fit great.  Was just hard to put on, have a stacked washer and gas drier, and was a pain chainging from the front,  but much cheaper than calling the appliance man out.

reviewText:
Replace this belt for my Maytag dryer
Still working good. No complain
You should buy a set ( pulley, belt..) so save your time when repair dryer or time to tune up.
The parts are link together so you replace at same time like belt, pulley...

Fit perfectly for our counter depth Samsung side by side.  This is absolutely the one that is 18 inches across - the dimenstions are wrong in the description.  It fits a gallon sized container of milk and comes complete with the clear guard and the white plastic bottom.  Good price and shipped fast.
summary: Perfect Fit for Counter Depth Samsung Side By Side

reviewText: Got it and it matched my brand new GE staove. Easy, cleans fast...LOVE IT. Company good and promt got it very quickly!BP3600 Range Oven Porcelain Broil Broiler Pan and Rack

my original(different brand of dishwasher) basket, had several breakes in the bottom from placing silverware in it, only have had this a few months so I don't know the longevity, but it appears to be good quality

previously purchased non-stick unit and immediately started losing coating was supposed to last for 5 yrs. this is the tried and true enameled
coating of my mother and grandmothers .easy to scrub and clean with oven cleaner. still perfect after several months of use

reviewText: Quality and capability are good, exactly as I was hoping.  Mostly a bacon pan for me, and fits in a standard size over just fine.  Easy to clean, dishwasher safe.  Arrived in great shape, no chips etc.  Feels like good old school construction.

Item arrived very quickly and described as indicated! I bought two (large) and the quality is the same it has been for years. My old ones have seen better days! There is a larger size than this. I also ordered the  Xlarge size for family gathering from another seller!

This hood is beautiful and it sits nice love the led lights
At first i was worried that it won't fit or that its cheaply made but i was wrong the seller shipped the item fast which is a bonus you do need an installer because the manual doesnt help at all
Over all im happy that i bought it

Arrived as prommised. Looks very good in our kitchen. It is as quiet as advertised. All functions work as described. I installed it myself and found it easy and everything fit together without any problems. Great quality and bright lights.

trying to get my kitchen remodel it has been taking time. and more with defective items like the hood bought that came broken. notice it now that make to the point to install that hood a couple of months after buying it.

Perfect. Love the way it make my kitchen look. We still have to patch up holes from our microwave mount and cupboard but and add backsplash but it already brighten my kicthen by so much already. Love it.

Beautiful.  It looks great.  I will say the fan is loud but then again in a noisy kitchen, who cares.  The 2 LED light in the rear half a nice and bright and it makes for a good kitchen evening light in the after dinner hours.
summary: Still very happy after a year and a half!

reviewText: I like the quality of this range hood. When my product came it had broken part behind touch panel, so I contacted seller and they shipped new part right away, got it installed and it works like a charm. Great company to deal with. I also recomened to my brother in law and he got one for himself, also happy with it.

Installed by a contractor, it looks great, has a powerful fan, and spot lights emit a beautful glow on to our stove top oven. The price was considerbly less than all we had seen at even so called discount outlets. The delivery was well within the time frame listed. We are very happy witb this purchase. I will continue to look to Amazon for purchases I have not previously made online.

This thing is great. It looks every bit of the more expensive ones you see and love but cant afford. Installed super easy. And moves allot of air on top of it. Love the light from it also. All around great experience.

LOVE IT!  SOOOOO quiet in use and beautiful, modern addition to kitchen.  Easy slight-touch to turn-on all.  Note: The 2 lights are located in rear of glass panel. Lighting will spill-over on the front burners of stove.  Your other ceiling lights will fill-in...Looks great on our stone backsplash, tho!  GREAT PRODUCT. Need 2 people to install.

Ordered this fan for our kitchen renovation. Loved the price and were wondering if it would work and look as described. It did. Looks great, very good quality for the price. Glass is nice thickness and the fan is powerful and quiet. Would I buy it again. Absolutely.

I purchased this filter couple months ago thinking I will save some money. Wrong! the thing it very hard to install and after I got it in, it leaks. replaced with Samsung filter, no problem....Do Not!!!!! buy this filter.

This is my first and LAST water filter purchase from Amazon. This filter leaked for some time before I noticed it. The water pooled under the bottom drawer (I have a french door style Samsung). I ordered the 2 pack, thinking I would save a couple of bucks. This filter looks genuine, It has all the Samsung logo and numbers. Shame on you Amazon for selling fakes. Keep this up, and your reputation will take a much deserved noise dive.

Counterfeit filter - Leaks water into fridge and onto floor. This looks nearly identical to the original Samsung, except for subtle differences pointed out in other reviewers photos.

A year ago I bought one that was genuine... five stars there. This 1 star review is for the counterfeiters and Amazon for allowing this trash.

Haven't had working fridge water in forever. Moved into a new place and needed a replacement filter, got this one and hurrraaayyy good tasting cold water. Deeply prefer this to my mavea pitcher (which I was quite attached to) because I don't have to fill anything.

Have gotten this brand name in past with no issues; however, this last one started leaking from filter about a week after installation.  The females response... if its leaking... it must be something wrong with your fridge. Then proceeded to try and schedule a service technician.  Be aware... most customer service jobs are outsourced outside US where there is usually a huge language barrier.  Better off buying something like this locally just in case defective

This is the factory original filter for our refrigerator and installed in literally seconds with a half turn. A great buy on our part. FYI can go much longer than the refrigerators filter change reminder, as long as the water looks and tastes great still. I recommend it

I bought generic brands prior to purchasing these genuine Samsung water filters and totally regretted it! These kept the water tasting great for my household for over a year! Will definitely purchase these again!
summary: These kept the water tasting great for my household for over a year

reviewText: Recently replaced the filter to my Samsung french door refrigerator with no issues.  Make sure to turn the water to the house or refrigerator off first...then dispense the remaining water from the refrigerator.
summary: Recently replaced the filter to my Samsung french door refrigerator ...

reviewText: Purchased a two pack of these filters and by the end of December the second one is running very show and now needs to be replaced. This is on a public water system so really clean to begin with just a necessary part of the system if you want to use the water in the door feature of the refrigerator. So not one to write bad reviewed but this needed to be an exception.

Genuine brand products for Refrigerator's I have always had better luck with then off brand. These work great, longevity very good, since I have athletes in the home and lots of water, ice constantly being used.

Would rate zero stars if I could.  Water was awful- never got over a plastic chlorine type taste.  Gave it two months and gave up, replacing it with a culligan from the local ACE store.  Will never buy this again from Amazon

The water taste very good when it is filtered we always enjoy it the filters are a bit pricey , as we only got 6 months out of the original filter so basically $120 a year on filters to have fresh clean water

Looked around for these filters for my refrigerator.  Came in, fit fine and it is working.  Bonus, this is a 2 pack, which I apparently missed when I was ordering, so I have a spare for the next time the filter needs to be changed.
summary: fit fine and it is working

reviewText:
Expensive but convienant
I like the fact that this OEM product fits and doesnt leak like other reviews on a non-OEM filter. Worth the cost for having peace of mind its the right part and won't leak.
I haven't tried other brands but reviews Ive read, they are not positive. This is the 2nd filter now Ive purchased and both have been 100% exact fit.

I used an non=Samsung Water Filter and it caused my frigde to leak. Service person said to use only a Samsung in my appliance. I bought this one and found that the price was good and it stopped the leaking problem right away!

These filters are as described.  I had to chat with a representive from Samsung to know if this was the correct filter.  It is easy to change.  Came well packaged.  Matched the description.  Would purchase again.

After 5 months in use this filter has all but stopped the water flow from the dispenser. Filling a glass takes over a minute.  Just removed it and water came out like it should. We are on filtered city water so is virtually no sediments to remove. Rather than spending $50 every six months to reduce our waterflow to a trickle I think we will just skip it

Samsung rf28hfedbsr Refrigerator and Samsung Genuine DA29-00020B Filter

More affordable online than in my local hardware store. Genuine Samsung product. I will purchase them in the 4 pack next time. More bang for the buck! I would not recommend using the knock off product as it voids the warranty.  I mean unless you have lots of wealth, than no worries!

After two failed generic filter attempts where there was leaking from my Samsung fridge finally ended after a few days and bought this Brand filter! There is a difference between brand CS generic filters and worth paying more avoid water damage.

There is a line in an old Mae West movie where the man says, "This picture looks just like you!" Mae replies, "Well, it otta, I posed for it!"

This filter fits perfectly the first time, every time and has not leaked since installed three weeks ago. It's nice when you go to the trouble of purchasing OEM parts, the parts are the exactly the replacement part as advertised.

reviewText: Ok so we can all see the product picture and this as you can see it's not what arrived this is after I called to request a replacement I will be calling back again. I bought a filter to remove lead as described but wrong filter arrived Twice

Had purchased Home Depot replacements...bad mistake as the kitchen was flooded.  Repair man said that despite being "replacements", the grooves are off a bit.  Will only use the OEM replacement  from now on

Great filter. I was planning to opt cheaper filters but found that this was NSF53 grade. Its totally worth. My area water is very hard and this filters the water pretty good. The water tastes way better than how it tastes with Brita or Pur water filters. Good  investment even though its double the cost of filtes with lower NSF53 grade.

reviewText: I looked at the cheaper filters and reviews and elected to buy the real deal for my Samsung fridge..and glad I did.
